oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Confederate monument
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Black and white photograph of a Confederate monument in Jackson, Tennessee. The view is looking northeast from Market Street (now Highland Avenue.)
The Confederate monument is located in front of the Madison County Courthouse. The words "To the Confederate Dead of Madison County - Erected 1888."
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Monuments & memorials
